SIMPLE: inexorable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexorable
<hw>In*ex"o*ra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexorabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inexorable</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Exorable</er>, <er>Adore</er>.]</ety> <def>Not to be
persuaded or moved by entreaty or prayer; firm; determined; unyielding;
unchangeable; inflexible; relentless; -- of people and impersonal
forces; <as>as, an <ex>inexorable</ex> prince or tyrant; an
<ex>inexorable</ex> judge; the <ex>inexorable</ex> advance of a
glacier.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inexorable</xex> equality of
laws.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Gibbon.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Death's <xex>inexorable</xex>
doom.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are more inhuman, more <qex>inexorable</qex>,⟦br⟧
O, ten times more than tigers of Hyrcania.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexorableness</ent>⟦br⟧
